{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is the interaction between summary-persistence logic and stored per-dimension findings for the same round. A unit test of a pure checker could pass while wiring/query bugs still allow invalid PASS writes.","test_description":"Wire real summary-write service + findings repository (local test DB). Seed round R with at least one FAIL finding. Attempt to persist a PASS summary for round R. Assert write is rejected (error/result code), PASS summary is not stored, and existing findings remain unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a cross-module data-source correctness check: gate computation must read persisted findings, not summary text. The real defect appears when storage access and gate logic are wired together.","test_description":"Use real gate computation path with repository + summary store. Seed same round with summary text claiming PASS but persisted findings containing FAIL. Invoke stop-gate verdict computation. Assert verdict is non-PASS and trace/debug payload shows findings-derived decision path.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The behavior spans request validation plus audit-record emission/persistence. A unit test can miss failures where override flag handling and audit sink are miswired.","test_description":"Call summary-finalization endpoint/service twice against local DB: (1) manual override text without override flag, expect rejection and no override record; (2) same request with explicit override flag, expect acceptance and a persisted audit warning containing actor, round, timestamp, and reason.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the review loop cannot finalize PASS unless a fresh review-agent round is executed on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The core risk is orchestration/state consistency across diff versioning, phase transitions, and round records. Correctness does not depend on model output quality, only on presence/freshness checks.","test_description":"Set up workflow state with pre-fix review round and unresolved issues, then mark Phase 4 fixes applied with a new diff hash. Attempt PASS finalization without creating a new review round for the new hash; assert blocked. Then create a new round tied to updated hash and assert finalization can proceed (subject to findings).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings, the flow emits an escalation outcome instead of PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is policy evaluation over persisted round counters and findings severity. Real failures typically come from state aggregation across modules, not single-function logic alone.","test_description":"Configure max-rounds=N in test config. Seed rounds up to N with at least one unresolved MUST-FIX finding. Run end-of-loop decision step through real orchestrator + repository. Assert outcome is ESCALATION (or equivalent), PASS is never emitted, and escalation payload references unresolved MUST-FIX items.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
